For March, shortages and insufficient amounts of reagents affected mass testing in the European Union and the US.
This led some authors to explore sample preparation protocols involving heating samples to 98°C (208°F) for 5 minutes to release RNA genomes for further testing.On March 31, it was announced that the UAE was now doing more coronavirus screening per person in its population than any other country, and was on track to raise the level of testing to cover most of the population.
